studyDesigns.name: Study Design
studyDesigns.rationale: Protocol-defined study design for investigating efficacy and safety

arms.name: Placebo
arms.description: Single oral dose of placebo solution, administered under fasted conditions

arms.name: Moxifloxacin 400 mg
arms.description: Single oral dose of 1 moxifloxacin tablet (400 mg), administered under fasted conditions (open-label positive control)

arms.name: Evobrutinib 45 mg
arms.description: Single oral dose of evobrutinib (45 mg) solution, administered under fasted conditions (therapeutic dose)

arms.name: Evobrutinib 225 mg
arms.description: Single oral dose of evobrutinib (225 mg) solution, administered under fasted conditions (supratherapeutic dose)

objectives.name: Primary QTc Evaluation Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate whether evobrutinib administered as a single oral dose (as solution) of 45 mg or 225 mg prolongs QT/QTc in comparison to placebo control

objectives.name: Safety and Tolerability Objective
objectives.text: To assess the safety and tolerability of evobrutinib

objectives.name: ECG Parameters Objective
objectives.text: To assess the effect of evobrutinib on other ECG parameters

objectives.name: Pharmacokinetics Objective
objectives.text: To determine the PK of evobrutinib at 45 mg and 225 mg oral dose (solution) under fasting conditions and moxifloxacin at 400 mg oral dose

endpoints.name: Primary QTcF Endpoint
endpoints.text: ΔΔQTcF (placebo-corrected change from baseline QTcF) for evobrutinib; with concentration-QTc analysis as primary analysis

endpoints.name: Moxifloxacin QTcF Endpoint
endpoints.text: ΔΔQTcF (placebo-corrected change from baseline QTcF) for moxifloxacin

endpoints.name: Treatment-Emergent Adverse Events Endpoint
endpoints.text: Nature, occurrence, and severity of TEAEs

endpoints.name: Safety Laboratory Tests Endpoint
endpoints.text: Absolute values and changes in safety laboratory tests

endpoints.name: Vital Signs Endpoint
endpoints.text: Vital signs assessed from time of first dose to end of study participation

endpoints.name: Other ECG Parameters Endpoint
endpoints.text: QT, QTcB, QTcI, PR, QRS, RR, HR, cardiologist assessment including T-wave morphology, and U-wave

endpoints.name: Evobrutinib PK Endpoint
endpoints.text: AUC0-24, AUC0-∞, Cmax, and tmax for evobrutinib and major metabolite

endpoints.name: Moxifloxacin PK Endpoint
endpoints.text: AUC0-24, AUC0-∞, Cmax, and tmax for moxifloxacin

studyInterventions.name: Evobrutinib 45 mg

studyInterventions.name: Evobrutinib 225 mg
studyInterventions.description: Supratherapeutic dose of evobrutinib administered as oral solution under fasted conditions

studyInterventions.name: Placebo
studyInterventions.description: Matching placebo oral solution administered under fasted conditions

studyInterventions.name: Moxifloxacin 400 mg
studyInterventions.description: Positive control for QTc assay sensitivity administered as oral tablet under fasted conditions

activities.description: Obtain written informed consent prior to any screening activity

activities.name: Participants resident at CRU
activities.description: Participants resident at clinical research unit, discharge on Day 2 of each period

activities.name: Eligibility criteria
activities.description: Eligibility criteria assessment, recheck of health status on Day -1

activities.name: Demography, height & weight
activities.description: Demography to include, at minimum age (year of birth), sex, race, and ethnicity

activities.name: Viral serology, TSH, eGFR, QuantiFERON® test
activities.description: Viral serology, TSH, eGFR, QuantiFERON® test

activities.name: Cotinine, alcohol and drugs of abuse testing, SARS-CoV-2
activities.description: Cotinine, alcohol and drugs of abuse testing, SARS-CoV-2

activities.name: Physical examination
activities.description: Brief examination on Days -1 of each period to recheck eligibility/healthy state after return to CRU and on the End of Treatment assessment visit

activities.name: Vital signs
activities.description: Vital signs will be assessed on Day -1 of each period and on the days of dosing (Day 1 of each period) at predose and 1, 2, 6, and 24 h postdose. Body temperature will be assessed at Screening, predose, and the End of Treatment assessment visit.

activities.name: Safety ECGs
activities.description: Safety ECG at 2 h postdose in each period

activities.name: Holter recordings
activities.description: Holter recordings starting 1 hour prior to first timepoint on Day 1 and lasting at least until last timepoint of PK sampling on Day 2 (24 h postdose) of each period

activities.name: Triplicate ECGs from Holter recordings
activities.description: On each dosing day 12-lead ECGs extracted in triplicates from Holter recordings at 3 timepoints before dosing (-1 h, -30 min, and -10 min), and at 15 and 30 min and 1, 1.5, 2, 2.5 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16 h and at 24 h postdose

activities.name: Clinical laboratory safety tests
activities.description: Blood samples for the clinical laboratory safety assessments will be collected in a fasted condition

activities.name: PK sampling (evobrutinib, evobrutinib major metabolite, and moxifloxacin)
activities.description: Plasma samples for PK analysis will be collected on the days of dosing (i.e., Days 1, 8, 15, and 22) at predose and 15 and 30 min, and 1, 1.5, 2, 2.5, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16 and 24 h postdose

notes.text: a Assuming 7 days washout between treatment periods.
c Recheck of health status on Day -1.
d Body temperature will be assessed at Screening, predose, and the End of Treatment assessment visit.

CRU=clinical research unit; ECG=electrocardiogram; eGFR=estimated glomerular filtration rate; FSH=follicle stimulating hormone; PK=pharmacokinetics; SARS-CoV-2=severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2; TSH=thyroid stimulating hormone.

studyAmendments.summary: This non-substantial amendment was prepared to correct a typographical error in the schedule of activities. The PK sampling at 16 h postdose is not included in the schedule of activities, although the corresponding ECG measurement is included in the schedule of activities. The 16 h postdose blood sampling is present in Table 1 (Time Deviations from PK sampling times, Section 8.4.1) and is also consistently displayed in the ICF. Additionally, in Section 7.1 there was a harmonization with the preexisting next sentence. It was clarified, that if study intervention is permanently discontinued, the participant will remain in the study to be evaluated for safety assessments.

This non-substantial protocol amendment was prepared to allow rescreening of participants that were not previously enrolled in the study due to personal or logistical reasons or due to minor deviations that were not considered clinically relevant. Additional, wording of inclusion criteria was changed to have more flexibility regarding ratio of sexes.

conditions.name: ALT/AST Elevation Stopping Criteria
conditions.description: Liver safety stopping criteria based on ALT or AST elevation
conditions.text: All confirmed events of ALT or AST ≥ 5 × ULN triggers stopping criteria

conditions.name: ALT/AST with Bilirubin Elevation Stopping Criteria
conditions.description: Combined liver function test stopping criteria
conditions.text: All confirmed events of ALT or AST ≥ 3 × ULN and total bilirubin ≥ 2 × ULN triggers stopping criteria

conditions.name: QTcF Prolongation Stopping Criteria
conditions.description: Cardiac safety stopping criteria based on QTcF changes
conditions.text: Changes from baseline in QTcF > 60 ms and QT/QTcF > 500 ms

conditions.name: Severe Hypersensitivity Reaction
conditions.text: Clinical manifestations of severe hypersensitivity reactions or signs and symptoms of severe skin reactions

conditions.name: Eligibility Recheck
conditions.description: Health status recheck on Day -1 of each period
conditions.text: Recheck of health status on Day -1 before each treatment period

transitionRules.name: Screening to Treatment Period 1
transitionRules.text: Participant must meet all eligibility criteria and be randomized to treatment sequence

transitionRules.name: Treatment Period Transition
transitionRules.text: At least 7-day washout period between successive doses required before next treatment period

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Liver Safety
transitionRules.text: ALT or AST ≥ 5 × ULN or ALT/AST ≥ 3 × ULN with total bilirubin ≥ 2 × ULN requires treatment discontinuation

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Cardiac Safety
transitionRules.text: QTcF > 60 ms change from baseline and QT/QTcF > 500 ms requires investigator review for continuation

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Hypersensitivity
transitionRules.text: Severe hypersensitivity reactions or severe skin reactions require participant discontinuation from study

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Pregnancy
transitionRules.text: Pregnancy requires discontinuation of study intervention

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Severe AE
transitionRules.text: AEs of severe intensity and SAEs regardless of relationship to study intervention may require discontinuation

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Protocol Noncompliance
transitionRules.text: Protocol noncompliance judged as significant by the Investigator after discussion with Sponsor

transitionRules.name: Discontinuation for Prohibited Medication Use
transitionRules.text: Use of nonpermitted concomitant drug if clinically relevant as agreed by Sponsor and Investigator

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Lost to Follow-Up

scheduleTimelineExits.name: Eligibility Criteria Not Met Post-Enrollment
